<item>
            <title>[LU-11869] Whamcloud repo URL for 2.12 LTS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11869</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter,&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
We are in the process of switching from 2.10 LTS to 2.12 LTS on Sherlock (Lustre clients).&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
We like to use a single repo URL that doesn&#8217;t change across LTS versions, like &#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/latest-release/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/latest-release/&lt;/a&gt; for 2.10 LTS so that we automatically get updated packages when made available. We have reposync in place and compute nodes being redeployed quite often on this cluster so this way the cluster automatically gets updated lustre-client RPMs.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
As of today, 2.12.0 is available in&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;latest-feature-release/&lt;br/&gt;
and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.12.0/&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
But I assume that when 2.13 is out, it will land in latest-feature-release. We don&apos;t want to switch to 2.13 immediately when it&apos;s out but keep using 2.12.x&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
What wc repo can we use for 2.12.x LTS clients? If it doesn&apos;t exist yet, can you provide a single repo URL for it?&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks much!&lt;br/&gt;
Stephane&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
