                            <comment id="240354" author="sthiell" created="Fri, 18 Jan 2019 19:17:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Minh, that should help! It&apos;s just a bit curious that 2.12.0 not considered as LTS, I&apos;m not sure to understand that. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="240352" author="mdiep" created="Fri, 18 Jan 2019 18:48:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sthiell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sthiell&quot;&gt;sthiell&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a good question. latest-release is always pointing to &apos;latest LTS&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
 As of today, latest LTS = 2.10.6 and will be 2.12.1 when it&apos;s available&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have created two new links to make things easier&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;latest-2.10-release ---&amp;gt; 2.10.6 (today and will be 2.10.7 and so on)&lt;br/&gt;
 latest-2.12-release ---&amp;gt; 2.12.0 (today and will be 2.12.1 and so on)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="240179" author="pjones" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2019 02:31:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
